# Week 6 — IDS Monitoring Implementation

## Overview

Week 6 introduces **security monitoring capabilities** into the ICS-RedSim environment.
This phase focuses on deploying an Intrusion Detection System (IDS) to monitor industrial network traffic and detect suspicious activity.

The IDS used in this project is **Suricata**, which analyzes network packets and generates alerts when abnormal patterns are detected.

To centralize log monitoring and analysis, the IDS alerts were integrated with **Wazuh**.
This integration enables real-time security monitoring through a centralized dashboard.

---

# Objectives

The primary objectives of Week 6 include:

* Deploy a network intrusion detection system
* Monitor industrial network traffic
* Detect abnormal communication patterns
* Integrate IDS alerts with centralized logging
* Validate detection capabilities

---

# Security Monitoring Architecture

Security monitoring was implemented using a dedicated **Monitoring Zone** that observes communication within the OT network.

### Monitoring Workflow

```
SCADA (FUXA)
        |
        | Modbus TCP
        |
PLC (OpenPLC)
        |
        |
Network Traffic
        |
        v
Suricata IDS
        |
        |
Security Alerts
        |
        v
Wazuh Dashboard
```

This architecture allows network traffic to be inspected without interfering with the industrial process.

---

# Intrusion Detection System

The IDS deployed in the lab environment is **Suricata**.

Suricata provides the following capabilities:

* Deep packet inspection
* Protocol analysis
* Signature-based detection
* Real-time alert generation
* Network anomaly detection

Suricata continuously monitors industrial traffic and generates alerts when suspicious patterns are detected.

---

# Log Monitoring Platform

Security logs generated by Suricata were integrated into **Wazuh**.

Wazuh provides the following features:

* Centralized log management
* Security event monitoring
* Alert visualization
* Dashboard analytics

This integration enables security analysts to investigate alerts and analyze network activity.

---

# Network Traffic Monitoring

The monitoring system focuses on industrial network communication between the SCADA system and the PLC.

Key monitoring targets include:

* Modbus TCP communication
* Unauthorized connection attempts
* Network scanning activity
* Abnormal traffic patterns
* Unexpected protocol usage

These monitoring capabilities help detect suspicious activity within the ICS network.

---

# Detection Capabilities

The IDS system is configured to detect several types of suspicious activities.

### Example Detection Events

| Event Type                | Description                                  |
| ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Port Scan                 | Detection of network reconnaissance activity |
| Unauthorized Modbus Write | Unauthorized control commands                |
| Traffic Flood             | Abnormally high traffic volume               |
| Suspicious Connections    | Unknown devices accessing OT systems         |

These detections help identify potential security incidents.

